Parliament, Monday, 7 May 2018 – A joint meeting of the Portfolio Committee on Water and Sanitation and the Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow consider the terms of reference of the parliamentary inquiry into the challenges facing the Department of Water and Sanitation, focus areas and the draft programme for the joint committee. Details of meeting: Date: Tuesday, 8 May 2018
	Time: 10:00
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON WATER AND SANITATION, MR LULU JOHNSON, AND OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries, please contact the Committees’ Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
	Cell: 081 377 0686
